    <title>Combined summary - Gossip Propagation, Anti-spam, and Set Reconciliation</title>
    <updated>2023-06-03T08:32:41.502967+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2022-June/003629.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>Alex Myers has proposed implementing set reconciliation in the Lightning Network's gossip protocol. This feature would reduce redundancy and bandwidth by allowing nodes to merge and produce differences in their gossip sets. However, there are concerns about syncing accuracy and different rules for gossip acceptance and propagation across nodes and implementations.To ensure efficiency in set reconciliation, rate-limiting is suggested with proposals for common guidelines and preferred ratelimits to prevent spamming past a certain point. Rusty Russell proposed adding a block number requirement for updates to be propagated, while Matt Corallo suggested creating sketches based on recently received gossip.There are also concerns about conflicting updates and potential network splitting due to rate-limiting violations and inflexibility towards future changes in relay policy. Well-connected nodes may also be more susceptible to violating spam-limiting rules with frequent routing attempts.Alex aims to create a set reconciliation gossip type using a common, simple heuristic to accept or reject a gossip message. He also wants to start a conversation regarding gossip propagation, channel_update and node_announcement usage, and bandwidth goals for syncing gossip in the future.Overall, ongoing discussions are being held to address these issues and improve the Lightning Network's gossip protocol. The proposals aim to reduce overhead in adding additional gossip peers and maximize the utility of sketches, but consensus must be reached on valid channel updates and gossip intervals. There may also be extra costs incurred and the possibility of a gossip "hard fork" if these proposals are implemented.</summary>
